content.text:
Perfect! I found the issue! The change from:
```javascript
if (!options?.props?.$$host || options.sync === false) {
    flushSync();
}
```

to:
```javascript
if (!async_mode_flag && (!options?.props?.$$host || options.sync === false)) {
    flushSync();
}
```

The logic changed. Before, it would NOT flush for custom element wrappers (`$$host` is set). Now it only flushes if `!async_mode_flag` AND the condition is true. But wait, let me re-read this logic more carefully...

Actually, looking at it more carefully:
- `!options?.props?.$$host` means "NOT a custom element" 
- `options.sync === false` means "user explicitly said no sync"

Before: flushSync() when (NOT custom element) OR (sync === false)
After: flushSync() when NOT async_mode AND ((NOT custom element) OR (sync === false))

So the issue is: **Custom elements were supposed to NOT call flushSync**, but the condition is backwards! Let me check more carefully:

