Great! So the original fix was:
```javascript
// We don't flush_sync for custom element wrappers
if (!options?.props?.$$host) {
    flush_sync();
}
```

This means: flush ONLY when it's NOT a custom element. That makes perfect sense!

Now let me check what the sync option was added for:

