OK! Now I see the bug! The condition changed from:
```javascript
if (!options?.props?.$$host) {
    flush_sync();
}
```

to:
```javascript
if (!options?.props?.$$host || options.sync === false) {
    flush_sync();
}
```

The bug is that `|| options.sync === false` should be `&& options.sync !== false`. Let me verify my understanding:

1. Custom elements should NOT flush sync (so we need `!$$host`)
2. If user sets `sync: false`, we should NOT flush sync
3. So we should flush when: NOT custom element AND sync is NOT false

The correct condition should be:
```javascript
if (!options?.props?.$$host && options.sync !== false) {
    flush_sync();
}
```

Let me create a test to reproduce the issue first:

