Actually, looking at the commit more carefully, it changed from `queue_micro_task` to `effect`. But `effect` in Svelte 5 is a reactive effect that runs when dependencies change. It's not synchronous either.

Wait, but the fix commit says it makes styles "available on mount". Let me re-read the test from that commit:

```javascript
await tick();
await tick();
await tick();

assert.ok(html.includes('<style'));
```

The test still waits for ticks! So even with the fix, styles aren't immediately available - they're just available sooner (in an effect vs microtask).

But the bug report says in version 5.35.7 it worked. Let me check what version is in testbed:

